{"Title": "Designing for inconsistency \u2013 the dependency-based PERICLES approach", "Year": 2015, "Source": "Commun. Comput. Info. Sci.", "Volume": "539", "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 458, "PageEnd": 467, "CitedBy": 13, "DOI": "10.1007/978-3-319-23201-0_46", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84946037224&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 Springer International Publishing Switzerland 2015.The rise of the Semantic Web has provided cultural heritage researchers and practitioners with several tools for ensuring semantic-rich representations and interoperability of cultural heritage collections. Although indeed offering a lot of advantages, these tools, which come mostly in the form of ontologies and related vocabularies, do not provide a conceptual model for capturing contextual and environmental dependencies contributing to long-term digital preservation. This paper presents one of the key outcomes of the PERICLES FP7 project, the Linked Resource Model, for modelling dependencies as a set of evolving linked resources. The proposed model is evaluated via a domain-specific representation involving digital video art.", "AuthorKeywords": ["Dependency", "Digital preservation", "Digital video art", "LRM", "Ontology"], "IndexKeywords": ["Conceptual model", "Cultural heritage collections", "Cultural heritages", "Dependency", "Digital preservation", "Digital videos", "Domain specific", "LRM"], "DocumentType": "Book Series", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 0, "EID": "2-s2.0-84946037224", "SubjectAreas": [["Computer Science (all)", "COMP", "1700"], ["Mathematics (all)", "MATH", "2600"]], "AuthorData": {"7007070993": {"Name": "Vion-Dury J.Y.", "AuthorID": "7007070993", "AffiliationID": "60022053", "AffiliationName": "Xerox Research Centre Europe (XRCE)"}, "9733514900": {"Name": "Lagos N.", "AuthorID": "9733514900", "AffiliationID": "60022053", "AffiliationName": "Xerox Research Centre Europe (XRCE)"}, "13408692000":